C-g -- quit
C-x C-c -- Exit
C-x C-f -- open
C-x k -- kill the buffer

Moving
C-f -- move forward one character
C-b -- move back one character
M-f -- move forward one word
M-b -- move back one word

C-d -- delete a character
M-d -- delete a word
C-_ -- undo

C-p -- previous line (up)
C-n -- next line (down)
C-a -- move to the beginning of a line (home)
C-e -- move to the end of a line (end)

M-< -- move to the beginning of the buffer
M-> -- move to the end of the buffer
C-v -- page down
M-v -- page up
C-l -- center the screen at line

Windows
C-x 2 -- Split the window vertically (top/bottom)
C-x 3 -- Split the window horizontally (left/right)
C-x 1 -- remove all other windows
C-x 0 -- remove this window
C-x o -- other window

Search
C-s -- text  <---- search
C-s -- Text  <---- case sensitive search
C-s -- toggle through instances of found text
M-x grep RET <search word> -- grep for <search word> in each file in directory

Marking
C-space -- start/toggle marking a region

Copy/Paste
C-w -- cut/kill
M-w -- copy
C-y -- yank/paste
C-k -- cut/kill to end of line
M-y -- (after C-y) cycles through previous killed/cut things
M-y -- (for me, for some reason) brings up ring of cut things

M-x query-replace -- search and replace with a query
M-% -- same as M-x query-replace
M-x replace-string -- replace all strings without a query
M-$ -- spell check word
M-x ispell-region -- spell check marked region
M-x ispell-buffer -- spell check buffer
M-x flyspell-mode -- turn on auto spellcheck (gui only?)

C-x b -- switch to a different buffer in a window (ibuffer for me)
M-x shell -- start a bash command line

M-u -- make upper case (from point to end of word)
M-l -- make lower case (from point to end of word)
M-c -- capitalize

M-x compile RET <command> -- run command ('./script.py' or 'make')
C-x ` -- jump to next error

Customization
C-x C-e -- execute all code up to point
M-x load-theme RET <theme> -- load theme
M-x customize-themes -- gui to try themes
M-x list-packages -- list packages (gnu/melpa)
